data.enText: I zipped the tent flaps shut.
movement

With a flap of its wings, the bird was gone.
the flap of the sails
worry/excitement

data.enText: She gets in a flap over the slightest thing.

phonetics
move quickly
if a bird flaps its wings, or if its wings flap , they move quickly up and down

data.enText: to move or to make sth move up and down or from side to side, often making a noise

data.chText: 两只大鸟振翅缓缓飞过水面。
data.enText: Two large birds flapped (= flew) slowly across the water.

data.chText: 她来回走动，挥动着双臂使身体暖和起来。
data.enText: She walked up and down, flapping her arms to keep warm.
A gust of wind flapped the tents.

data.chText: 不必担心——一切都已在我控制之中。

example: he wrote on the flap of the envelope

tr: a movable airfoil that is part of an aircraft wing

the motion made by flapping up and down

example: the waves rolled towards the beach
The eagle beat its wings and soared high into the sky

value.def: If something such as a piece of cloth or paper flaps or if you flap it, it moves quickly up and down or from side to side.

example.ex: Grey sheets flapped on the clothes line...
example.tran: 灰色的床单在晾衣绳上飘来摆去的。

example.ex: They would flap bath towels from their balconies as they chatted.
example.tran: 他们聊天时会在阳台上抖搂浴巾。

value.def: If a bird or insect flaps its wings or if its wings flap, the wings move quickly up and down.

example.ex: The bird flapped its wings furiously...
example.tran: 鸟儿使劲地扑打着翅膀。

example.ex: A pigeon emerges, wings flapping noisily, from the tower.
example.tran: 一只鸽子从塔里钻出来，扑扑地拍打着翅膀。

value.tran: 振(翅);挥(翅);(翅膀)拍打，抖动

value.def: If you flap your arms, you move them quickly up and down as if they were the wings of a bird.

example.ex: ...a kid running and flapping her arms.
example.tran: 边跑边挥舞着手臂的小孩子

value.def: A flap of cloth or skin, for example, is a flat piece of it that can move freely up and down or from side to side because it is held or attached by only one edge.

example.ex: He drew back the tent flap and strode out into the blizzard.
example.tran: 他拉开帐篷的门帘，大步走进暴风雪中。
耷拉着快要掉下的一块皮

value.tran: (布、皮等)扁平下垂物,垂下的部分

value.def: A flap on the wing of an aircraft is an area along the edge of the wing that can be raised or lowered to control the movement of the aircraft.

example.ex: ...the sudden slowing as the flaps were lowered.
example.tran: 襟翼放下时的突然减速

value.def: A flap is a sudden noise or movement made by a bird's wing or by a piece of paper or cloth when it flaps.

example.ex: Nothing to be heard but the soft flap of a silk banner.
example.tran: 万籁俱寂，只有一面绸制旗子轻轻飘动的响声。

value.tran: (鸟翼、布条、纸片的)拍打声，拍动，拍打

value.def: Someone who is in a flap is in a state of great excitement, worry, or panic.

example.ex: Why did people get in a flap over nuclear energy?...
example.tran: 为什么人们对核能惶恐不安呢？

example.ex: Wherever he goes there's always a flap.
example.tran: 无论他到哪里，都会引起一阵骚动。

trans: (门上供家猫进出的)活动板猫洞
